5528750,-0.03369512,0.00641607,0.00197372,0.04217737,-0.01742586,0.00253595,0.04243863,0.05228237,-0.03509153,0.00900436,-0.03098656,0.00202813,-0.00947403,0.07552906,0.04160842,0.04651958,-0.01072924,-0.06458293,-0.02192247,0.00114721,0.02557219,0.01069262,-0.12822337,-0.01836416,-0.03376379,-0.02699359,-0.06697986,-0.02799837,-0.01321302,0.03628061,-0.02982458,0.03108255,-0.02728551,-0.01939051,-0.02521420,0.04128800,0.05455085,0.04951378,-0.01894607,0.08613925,0.03090772,-0.00311570]',E'configs\n\nConfigs allow services to adapt their behaviour without the need to rebuild a Docker image. \nServices can only access configs when explicitly granted by the `configs` attribute. Two different syntax variants are supported.\n\nCompose reports an error if `config` doesn''t exist on the platform or isn''t defined in the\n[`configs` top-level element](08-configs.md) in the Compose file.\n\nThere are two syntaxes defined for configs. To remain compliant to this specification, an implementation\nmust support both syntaxes. Implementations must allow use of both short and long syntaxes within the same document.\n\nYou can grant a service access to multiple configs, and you can mix long and short syntax.','{"source": "docker", "version": "27", "language": "yaml", "title": "The Compose Specification", "section_title": "spec", "url": "https://github.com/compose-spec/compose-spec/blob/main/spec.md", "topics": "docker,compose,services,spec", "categories": "devops,containers,orchestration"}');
