11061,0.00014183,0.05248851,-0.00212388,0.02942825,-0.02720460,0.03386797,-0.00938442,-0.00300723,0.07378653,0.05149603,-0.04623491,-0.00545767,0.02196849,0.03183946,-0.00348314,0.04683355,-0.05335240,-0.03196946,0.00238542,-0.03061128,0.06351697,-0.03095774,-0.02923045,-0.03988822,-0.00485879,0.03379085,-0.00149083,-0.10960153,0.04899193,0.01142863,-0.01576644,-0.02017185,0.01491605,0.00619231,0.01097537,0.04351401,0.02228160,-0.04006290,0.07755697,0.06685215,-0.06416818]',E'Long syntax\n\nService dependencies cause the following behaviors:\n\n- Compose creates services in dependency order. In the following\n  example, `db` and `redis` are created before `web`.\n\n- Compose waits for healthchecks to pass on dependencies\n  marked with `service_healthy`. In the following example, `db` is expected to\n  be "healthy" before `web` is created.\n\n- Compose removes services in dependency order. In the following\n  example, `web` is removed before `db` and `redis`.','{"source": "docker", "version": "27", "language": "yaml", "title": "The Compose Specification", "section_title": "spec", "url": "https://github.com/compose-spec/compose-spec/blob/main/spec.md", "topics": "docker,compose,services,spec", "categories": "devops,containers,orchestration"}');
