002,-0.02942951,-0.00420560,0.01175639,-0.01179648,0.01513028,-0.00152222,0.09499305,-0.03654660,-0.04475263,0.05990740,-0.06038227,0.00313948,0.05768821,0.04127829,-0.01260773,0.02954893,0.02520210,-0.01495652,-0.01538728,-0.01390787,0.02247353,0.00121209,-0.02626125,-0.02179560,-0.04786526,-0.05942052,0.01802822,-0.00718337,-0.04562644,0.04716624,-0.04576587,0.03154889,-0.02693428,-0.02040007,-0.04594727,-0.04524852,0.01606998,0.03374733,0.00719295,0.02339301,0.04729265,0.03533040]',E'gpus\n\n[![Compose v2.30.0](https://img.shields.io/badge/compose-v2.30.0-blue?style=flat-square)](https://github.com/docker/compose/releases/v2.30.0)\n\n`gpus` specifies GPU devices to be allocated for container usage. This is equivalent to a [device request](deploy.md#devices) with\nan implicit `gpu` capability.\n\n```yaml\nservices:\n  model:\n    gpus: \n      - driver: 3dfx\n        count: 2\n```\n\n`gpus` also can ge set as string `all` to allocate all aviable GPU devices to container.\n\n```yaml\nservices:\n  model:\n    gpus: all\n```','{"source": "docker", "version": "27", "language": "yaml", "title": "The Compose Specification", "section_title": "spec", "url": "https://github.com/compose-spec/compose-spec/blob/main/spec.md", "topics": "docker,compose,services,spec", "categories": "devops,containers,orchestration"}');
