087426,-0.04296701,0.06209057,0.00613349,-0.03564906,0.04837221,-0.02003162,0.06718764,0.00021379,-0.05585413,-0.01015906,-0.05061429,0.02669523,-0.00375396,0.08057358,-0.02959739,0.01130818,0.00822813,-0.06672892,-0.04145675,-0.07726589,0.02995574,-0.00042895,0.00929230,-0.03076569,-0.00519708,0.03371286,0.01323565,-0.03853787,-0.04405370,0.03109897,-0.03592062,-0.00218572,-0.02321422,0.00136259,0.00251210,-0.06276830,0.01057139,0.01200171,-0.03095907,0.04431401,-0.01194991,0.03072240]',E'interface_name\n\n![Compose v2.36.0](https://img.shields.io/badge/compose-v2.36.0-blue?style=flat-square)](https://github.com/docker/compose/releases/v2.36.0)\n\n`interface_name` can be used to declare the network interface name used to connect to a target network. This\nallows you to enforce a deterministic assignment of network interface names for configured networks.\n\n```yaml\nservices:\n  backend:\n    image: alpine\n    command: ip link show\n    networks:\n      back-tier:\n        interface_name: eth0\n```\n\nRunning this Compose application shows:\n\n```console\nbackend-1  | 11: eth0@if64: <BROADCAST,MULTICAST,UP,LOWER_UP,M-DOWN> mtu 1500 qdisc noqueue state UP \n```','{"source": "docker", "version": "27", "language": "yaml", "title": "The Compose Specification", "section_title": "spec", "url": "https://github.com/compose-spec/compose-spec/blob/main/spec.md", "topics": "docker,compose,services,spec", "categories": "devops,containers,orchestration"}');
