2519,0.11310819,0.02732056,-0.01390540,0.05506926,0.04613066,0.07418451,0.07144249,0.02671587,-0.01073944,-0.01750005,0.06659617,-0.03002713,0.05162598,0.02254366,-0.02572935,-0.00475803,0.06762345,0.04751703,-0.00640985,-0.01948021,-0.03277479,0.00607081,0.06654714,-0.00630919,0.03907552,-0.04419059,-0.01694711,-0.00937018,-0.03358139,-0.00264085,0.04421014,-0.02697434,0.00534701,0.04334837,-0.02845478,-0.07929318,-0.03347796,0.00628253,0.03115372,0.03343196,-0.01029145,-0.01486368,-0.00550708]',E'memswap_limit\n\n- If `memswap_limit` is set to a positive integer, then both `memory` and `memswap_limit` must be set. `memswap_limit` represents the total amount of memory and swap that can be used, and `memory` controls the amount used by non-swap memory. So if `memory`="300m" and `memswap_limit`="1g", the container can use 300m of memory and 700m (1g - 300m) swap.\n- If `memswap_limit` is set to 0, the setting is ignored, and the value is treated as unset.','{"source": "docker", "version": "27", "language": "yaml", "title": "Services top-level element", "section_title": "05-services", "url": "https://github.com/compose-spec/compose-spec/blob/main/05-services.md", "topics": "docker,compose,services,05,services", "categories": "devops,containers,orchestration"}');
