55,-0.00773040,0.02749812,-0.02101396,-0.04036729,0.10479743,-0.01999680,0.02855938,0.06194419,-0.02868960,0.03016965,-0.01267578,-0.00938348,-0.02821360,0.05378627,0.01465043,-0.01458050,-0.02098806,-0.05888874,-0.01782682,-0.06409544,-0.00854335,0.03332386,-0.00898169,-0.05742000,-0.03401352,0.02192941,0.03384262,-0.01070881,-0.07938094,0.06298362,-0.00464506,0.02190850,-0.00670649,0.03240898,0.02382535,-0.04667138,0.01844682,0.01744369,0.00040487,0.09102519,0.01278458,0.04175946]',E'priority\n\n`priority` indicates in which order Compose connects the service’s containers to its\nnetworks. If unspecified, the default value is 0.\n\n_If the container runtime accepts a `mac_address` attribute at service level, it is\napplied to the network with the highest `priority`. In other cases, use attribute\n`networks.mac_address`._\n\n_`priority` does not affect which network is selected as the default gateway. Use the\n[`gw_priority`](#gw_priority) field for that._\n\n_`priority` does not control the order in which networks connections are added to\nthe container, it cannot be used to determine the device name (`eth0` etc.) in the\ncontainer._\n\n```yaml\nservices:\n  app:\n    image: busybox\n    command: top\n    networks:\n      app_net_1:\n        priority: 1000\n      app_net_2:\n\n      app_net_3:\n        priority: 100\nnetworks:\n  app_net_1:\n  app_net_2:\n  app_net_3:\n```','{"source": "docker", "version": "27", "language": "yaml", "title": "Services top-level element", "section_title": "05-services", "url": "https://github.com/compose-spec/compose-spec/blob/main/05-services.md", "topics": "docker,compose,services,05,services", "categories": "devops,containers,orchestration"}');
