8,0.17108795,-0.02852951,0.01296682,0.02909138,0.04127328,0.00630443,-0.01442052,0.05128354,0.09690232,-0.04494179,0.00633519,0.00750190,0.00767741,0.00713175,0.09022801,0.02240279,0.07623578,-0.05161408,-0.06222947,0.02275801,-0.04920821,0.02442200,0.00904956,-0.12154947,-0.04725660,-0.07853213,0.03433278,0.01237267,-0.02318286,-0.01329244,0.05194005,-0.00297869,-0.00243913,-0.00386402,-0.01591394,-0.04815838,0.04459493,0.03776623,0.04959924,0.00356202,0.09743775,0.01031375,0.06795304]',E'Configs top-level element\n\nConfigs allow services to adapt their behaviour without the need to rebuild a Docker image.\n\nServices can only access configs when explicitly granted by a [`configs`](05-services.md#configs) attribute within the `services` top-level element.\n\nAs with volumes, configs are mounted as files into a service''s container''s filesystem. The location of the mount point within the container defaults to `/<config-name>` in Linux containers and `C:\\<config-name>` in Windows containers.','{"source": "docker", "version": "27", "language": "yaml", "title": "Configs top-level element", "section_title": "08-configs", "url": "https://github.com/compose-spec/compose-spec/blob/main/08-configs.md", "topics": "docker,compose,services,08,configs", "categories": "devops,containers,orchestration"}');
